<br>
1.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Problem: range. </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> it seems to have none at all.  like 2 feet away is too far.  the concept of a short range makes sense, but really, this is TOO short. summoning, melee &quot;pushing&quot;, etc, all serve to break most uses of shield WELL before the already short duration is expired.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Solution: please consider expanding the range a bit.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
2.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Problem: chat window filtering</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> for some inexplicable reason, the /shield messages go into the same window as &quot;my hits&quot; and &quot;my misses&quot;.  this is a major problem for anyone who uses the &quot;number only&quot; option for hits and misses, as it puts a long text message into a narrow window.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Solution:  please filter these messages with melee /discs or with spell effects or with skills, not with hits/misses</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
<br>
3.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Problem: complete lack of damage reduction information</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  so... im taking some of Soandso's damage, as i just typed in /shield soandso.  so why can i NOT see any hits on my screen?  perhaps this is again related to using the hitsmode workaround or something, but if this is by design, please change it so that when i shield someone, i see MELEE hits displayed, instead of invisible damage being removed from my hp.  (not having been on the recieving end of shield, i dont know yet if the reduction in damage is visible there)<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Soltuion: make the damage all visible as melee damage. </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
<br>
4.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Problem:  the invisible 3 minute timer</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->so... i shielded this guy X minutes ago... is the shield skill useable again?  there is currently no way to find out other than typeing shield in again.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Solution:  make the shield skill a skill button just like Hide and Backstab, so that we can watch for it to ungrey.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
overall i really like it, but making the effects of shield more visible would help everyone.  and the chat filtering thing HAS to go, not being able to see the shield messages really blows. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ufoolsfizzelmore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fools Fizzelmore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 154<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/17/02 11:31:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2251.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bugs/Design Problems with /shield</span><hr size=1> nice to see some positive feedback about shield.<br>
